• What are the benefits of using CSS?
-> (1) FASTER PAGE SPEED.MORE CODE MEANS SLOWER PAGE SPEED.
   (2) BETTER USER EXPERIENCE.CSSNOT ONLY MAKESNWEB PAGE EASY ON THE EYE,IT ALSO ALLOWS FOR USER-FRIENDLY FORMATTING
   (3) QUICKER DEVELOPMENT TIME.
   (4) EASY FORMATTING CHANGES.
   (5) COMPATIBILITY  ACROSS DEVICES.

• What are the disadvantages of CSS?
-> (1) CONFUSION DUE TO MANY CSS LEVELS BEGINNERS ARE MORE VANERABLE TO THIS ISSUE..
   (2) CROSS-BROWSER ISSUES.DIFFERENT BROWERS WORK DIFFERENTLY.
   (3) SECURITY ISSUES.SECURITY IS IMPORTANT IN TODAY'S WORLD DRIVEN BY TECHNOLOGY AND DATA.
   (4) EXTRA WORK FOR DEVELOPERS.

• What is the difference between CSS2 and CSS3?
-> THE DIFFERENCE BETWWEN CSS2 AND CSS3 IS THAT CSS3 HAS BEEN SPLIT INTO DIFFERENT SECTIONS,CALLED MODULES.

• Name a few CSS style components
-> (1) SELECTER. HTML ELEMENT NAME,ID NAME CLASS NAME.
   (2) PROPERTY: IT'S LIKE AN ATTRIBUTES SUCH AS BACKGROUND COLOUR,FONT-SIZE,POSITIO,TEXT-ALIGN,COLOR,BORDER ETC.
   (3) VALUES- WHICH DEFINES PROPERTY OR VALUES ALLOCATE FOR PROPERTIES.

• What do you understand by CSS opacity?
-> THE DEGREE TO WHICH CONTENT6 BEHIMD AN ELEMENT IS HIDDEN,AND IS THE OPPOSITE OF TRANSPARENCY.

• How can the background color of an element be changed?
-> TO ADD BACKGROUND COLOR IN HTML, USE THE CSS BACKGROUND-COLOUR PROPERTY.

• How can image repetition of the backup be controlled?
-> THIS TASK CAN BE ACHIEVED BY USING THE BACKGROUND-REPEAT PROPERTY THST WILL HELP US TO CONTROL THE REPETITION OF THE IMAGE.

• What is the use of the background-position property?
->  THE BACKGROUND-POSITION PROPERTY SETS THE STARTING POSITION OF A BACKGROUND IMAGE.

• Which property controls the image scroll in the background? 
-> THE BACKGROUND-ATTACHMENT PROPERTY SETS WHETHER BACHGROUND IMAGE SCROLLS WITH THE REST OF THE PAGE,OR IS FIXED

• Why should background and color be used as separate properties?
-> THERE  ARE TWO REASONS BEHIND THIS ; ITS ENHANCES THE LEGIBILITY OF STYLE SHEETS.
• How to center block elements using CSS1?
-> WE CAN SIMPLY MAKE USE OF THE <CENTER> TAG

• How to maintain the CSS specifications?
->  THE CSS SPECIFICATIONS ARE MAINTAINED BY 'THE WORLD WIDE WEB CONSORTIUM (W3C)'

• What are the ways to integrate CSS as a web page?
->  TO STYLE A SINGLE HTML ELEMENT ON THE PAGE, USE INLINE CSS IN A STYLE ATTRIBUTE.
   
• What is embedded style sheets?
-> EMBEDDED STYLESHEET: IT ALLOWS YOU TO DEFINE STYLES FOR A PARTICULAR HTML DOCUMENT AS A WHOLE IN ONE PLACE.
   THIS IS DONE BY EMBEDDING THE <STYLE></STYLE> TAGS CONTAINING THE CSS PROPERTIES IN THE HEAD OF YOUR DOCUMENT.

• What are the external style sheets?
-> AN EXTERNAL STYLE SHEETS IS A SEPARATES CSS FILE THAT CAN BE ACCESSED BY CREATING A LINMK WITHIN IN THE HEAD  SECTION OF THE PAGE.

• What are the advantages and disadvantages of using external style sheets?
-> (1) ONE CHANGES TO THE STYLE SHEETS WILL CHANGE ALL LINKED PAGES.
   (2) YOU CAN CREATE CLASSES OF STYLES THAT CAN THEN BE USED ON MANY DIFFERENT HTML ELEMENTS.
   (3) CONSISTENT LOOK AND FEEL ACROSS MULTIPLE WEB PAGES.
   (4) IMPROVED LOAD TIMES BECAUSE THE CSS FILE IS DOWNLOADED ONCE AND APPLIED TO EACH RELEVANT PAGE AS NEEDED.

• What is the meaning of the CSS selector?
->  A CSS  SELECTOR IS THE FIRST PART OF A CSS RULE.IT IS A PATTERN OF ELEMENTS AND OTHER TERMS THAT TELL THE BROWSER WHICH HTML ELEMENTS SHOULD BE SELECTED TO       HAVE THE CSS PROPERTY VALUES INSIDE THE RULE APPLIED TO THEM.

• What are the media types allowed by CSS?
-> THERE ARE TYPES ALLOWED BY CSS MEDIA TYPES (1). PAINTING (2). COMPUTER MONITOR (3). TV (4). PAPER EMBOSSING (5). BRAILLE (6). COLOR (7). MONOCHROME (8). SPEECH

• What is the rule set?
-> DEFINATIONS:- A TABLE OF INSTRUCTIONS USED BY A CONTROLLED INTERFACE TO DETERMINE WHAT DATA IS ALLOWED AND HOW THE DATA IS HANDLED BETWEEN INTERCONNECTED SYSTEMS.

